# Tokenomics

Tokenomics defines how GGUILD is structured, distributed, and sustained over time.

The purpose of the tokenomics model is not merely to allocate supply, but to shape behavior, support stability, and reinforce the long-term mission of the ecosystem.

## Proposed Total Supply

Total Supply: 1,000,000,000 GGUILD

This number may be revised based on technical, community, and governance considerations, but it provides a scalable base model for a gaming-oriented ecosystem.

## Example Allocation Framework

- 40% Community Rewards
- 20% Treasury
- 20% Ecosystem Growth
- 10% Team and Builders
- 10% Reserve

## Allocation Logic

### Community Rewards
This portion supports the contributor economy. It is intended to reward actions that increase ecosystem value, such as content creation, moderation, growth, event participation, and community support.

### Treasury
The treasury exists to support the durability of the ecosystem. It may fund operations, tools, partnerships, grants, development, and growth campaigns under approved governance frameworks.

### Ecosystem Growth
This allocation is designed to support expansion. It may be used for launch campaigns, partnerships, onboarding incentives, creator collaborations, or community acquisition efforts.

### Team and Builders
This portion compensates the core contributors, developers, operators, and strategic builders behind the project. Vesting structures should be used to align long-term incentives.

### Reserve
The reserve provides optionality and resilience. It can help manage future needs, unforeseen events, strategic initiatives, or structural redesigns.

## Tokenomics Principles

The tokenomics model should aim for:

- clarity
- sustainability
- transparency
- anti-dump protections where appropriate
- long-term contributor alignment
- flexible but documented governance controls